des:
Enhance your Smart Home experience with Amazon Alexa and Nooie's products.

If you own an Alexa Echo Show, you can ask Alexa Echo Show to display the live view from your Nooie Cam.

Follow the steps here to connect your Nooie account to Amazon Alexa:
1. Download the "Nooie" app from the app store;
2. Register a Nooie account to add your devices;
3. Configure your devices and name the devices;
4. Download the "Amazon Alexa" app from the app store;
5. Configure Alexa Echo Show in the "Amazon Alexa" app;
6. Search for "Nooie" from the skills category in the "Amazon Alexa" app;
7. Enable "Nooie" skill, and you'll be navigated to Nooie's login page;
8. Log into your Nooie account to finish.

Once the "Nooie" Skill is enabled, simply ask Alexa to control your Nooie devices by their names. For example:
“Alexa, show (name of device)"
“Alexa, stop"

Currently this skill supports:
Nooie Cam 360（version ≥ 1.3.81）
Nooie Cam Outdoor（version ≥ 2.1.62）
Nooie Cam Indoor 1080P (version ≥ 2.1.90)

If you experience any problems while using this skill, please contact us at support@nooie.com
